      <li id="c4373229018691892693"><a name="c4373229018691892693"></a>
        <div class="comment-body">
         <p>Hi Mark.<BR/><BR/>Yeah, the white is very readable.  For whatever it's worth, colorblindness doesn't mean that I can't see color, just that it's difficult to distinguish certain colors.  Also, there are a number of types of colorblindness.  Check out <A HREF="http://colorvisiontesting.com/what%20colorblind%20people%20see.htm" REL="nofollow">this colorblindness info page</A> to see what it is.  If you're designing color palettes you should look at <A HREF="http://wellstyled.com/tools/colorscheme2/index-en.html" REL="nofollow">this website color generator tool</A> which can helpfully show a non-deficient individual what they're designing through the eyes of a colorblind person.</p>
        </div>
