      <li id="c4140402119939556303"><a name="c4140402119939556303"></a>
        <div class="comment-body">
         <p>My intuition tells me that this palette is perfectly counterproductive. What's needed is just a little bit of study rather than seat of your pants thinking, before recommending this approach. From studies of human perception, white on black is well understood to be harder and slower to read. In one such study, described at TreeHugger, "12 of the 15 subjects did read faster from [black on white] screens." I expect this means that it's likely your users will spend more time using the computer to read a Web site designed with this type of palette  (including rubbing their eyes rather than reading), and have their computer spend more energy doing so.</p>
        </div>
