      <li id="c4125519904699758426"><a name="c4125519904699758426"></a>
        <div class="comment-body">
         <p>Right color means a lot in web design. I'm fond of <A HREF="http://amolife.com/psychology/color-psychology-express-your-color-mood.html" REL="nofollow">color psychology</A>, so I choose them by intuition...</p>
        </div>
        <p class="comment-data">By <span style="line-height:16px" class="comment-icon blogger-comment-icon"><img src="http://img2.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif" alt="Blogger" style="display:inline;" /></span>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/12405298981801420560" rel="nofollow">Valery</a>, at <a href="#c4125519904699758426" title="comment permalink">7:00 AM</a>
	  <span class="item-control blog-admin pid-1901996319"><a style="border:none;" href="http://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.g?blogID=30452117&postID=4125519904699758426" title="Delete Comment" ><span class="delete-comment-icon">&nbsp;</span></a></span></p>
      </li>
      
    </ul>
	
